// frame_diag.su — DIAGONAL GRADIENT: a corner-to-corner ramp as a whole-frame field.
//
// GUI shapes increment. The diagonal cousin of frame_rgb.su's horizontal `gradient`:
//
//   diag = 0.5 * (1 + 0.5 * (x + y))   — 0 at the top-left corner (x = y = -1),
//                                        0.5 on the anti-diagonal (x + y = 0),
//                                        1 at the bottom-right corner (x = y = +1).
//
// One substrate op over the coordinate grid; `half` is the same host-provided
// constant buffer frame_rgb.su uses (there is no literal-times-buffer — `*` is the
// complex product, so scalars enter as buffers).
function vector diag(vector x, vector y, vector ones, vector half) {
    return hadamard(half, ones + hadamard(half, x + y));
}

// Sanity entry: the bottom-right corner (1, 1) -> 0.5 * (1 + 0.5 * 2) = 1.
function vector main() {
    return diag(make_real(1.0), make_real(1.0), make_real(1.0), make_real(0.5));
}
